content: I cannot predict the future, but it seems unlikely that high-speed trains will completely replace traditional trains. traditional trains play an important role in transporting both passengers and cargo, especially in areas where high-speed rail is not available or cost-effective. additionally, high-speed trains require significant infrastructure and investment, which may not be practical or feasible in all areas. however, high-speed trains can serve as a complement to traditional trains by offering faster travel times on certain routes and reducing traffic congestion on highways and in airports.
